Analysis

David John Baker

09/06/2020

Introduction

This document provides the analysis for Lyrics Emotional Influences in Songs: A Conceptual Replication of Ali and Peynirciolus (2006) Study. The script creates both figures for the paper as well as the statistical analysis.

Software Import

EDA Viz

Below are some of the working figures for the document.

# Plot of 4x2 ANOVA
valence_table <- tribble(
  ~valence, ~response,
  "Positive", "Happy",
  "Positive", "Calm",
  "Negative", "AngryStressful",
  "Negative", "Sad"
)

std <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))

(master_data %>%
  select(subject, Happy:AngryStressful, Condition) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = Happy:AngryStressful, names_to = "response",values_to = "rating") %>%
  group_by(Condition, response) %>%
  summarise(mean_rating = mean(rating),
            sd_rating = sd(rating),
            max_rating = max(rating),
            min_rating = min(rating),
            se_rating = std(rating),
            number_of_ratings = n()) %>%
  left_join(valence_table) %>%
  mutate(response = factor(response, levels = c("Happy","Calm","AngryStressful","Sad"))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = response, y = mean_rating, fill = valence)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  facet_wrap(~Condition) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_rating + se_rating, ymax = mean_rating - se_rating)) + 
  labs(title = "Mean Rating Per Condition",
       subtitle = "Error Bars are Standard Error of Mean",
       x = "Response Category",
       y = "Mean Rating") +
  theme_minimal() -> factorial_plot)
## Joining, by = "response"

master_data %>%
  select(subject, Happy:AngryStressful, Condition) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = Happy:AngryStressful, names_to = "response",values_to = "rating") %>%
  group_by(Condition, response) %>%
  summarise(mean_rating = mean(rating),
            sd_rating = sd(rating),
            max_rating = max(rating),
            min_rating = min(rating),
            se_rating = std(rating),
            number_of_ratings = n()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = response, y = mean_rating, color = Condition)) +
  geom_point(stat = "identity") +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = mean_rating + se_rating, ymax = mean_rating - se_rating)) + 
  labs(title = "Mean Rating Per Condition",
       subtitle = "Error Bars are Standard Error of Mean",
       x = "Response Category",
       y = "Mean Rating") +
  theme_minimal()

Replication of Pre-Registered Analysis

Below Analysis Includes

  • [X] 4x2 ANOVA
  • [X] Interaction Effects
  • [X] Main Effects of Lyrics and Emotion
  • [ ] Planned Contrast of Lyrics Making Positive Worse, Negative Better
  • [X] Correlate GMSI General with Emotional Ratings
  • [X] Correalte GMSI Emotional with Emotional Ratings
library(ez)
## Registered S3 methods overwritten by 'lme4':

##   cooks.distance.influence.merMod car

options(scipen = 999)

long_master_data <- master_data %>%
  select(subject, Happy:AngryStressful, Condition, title) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = Happy:AngryStressful, names_to = "response",values_to = "rating")

factorial_anova <- ezANOVA(
  data = long_master_data
  , dv = .(rating)
  , wid = .(subject)
  , within = .(Condition, response),
  type = 3, # Do you want to do Type III sum of Squares, doesnt change results...
  detailed = TRUE,
  return_aov = TRUE
)

GMSI Correlations

# As Univariate 
collapsed_emotion_ratings <- master_data %>%
  select(subject, Happy:AngryStressful) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = Happy:AngryStressful, names_to = "response",values_to = "rating") %>%
  group_by(subject) %>%
  summarise(mean_rating = mean(rating),
            sd_rating = sd(rating),
            max_rating = max(rating),
            min_rating = min(rating),
            se_rating = std(rating),
            number_of_ratings = n())

master_data %>%
  select(subject, GENERAL, EMOTIONS) %>%
  distinct() %>%
  left_join(collapsed_emotion_ratings, by = "subject") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = GENERAL, y = mean_rating)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  labs(title =  "Average Rating by General Scale",
       x = "GMSI General Score",
       y = "Mean Rating") +
  theme_minimal()
